---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Getting Started - CoderClaw Docs" description="Get up and running with CoderClaw in minutes. Install the CLI, create your first autonomous agent, and start orchestrating sub-agents with CoderClawLink.">
  <main class="docs-container">
    <aside class="docs-sidebar">
      <div class="sidebar-group">
        <h3 class="sidebar-title">Getting Started</h3>
        <nav class="sidebar-nav">
          <a href="/docs/getting-started" class="sidebar-link active">Quick Start</a>
          <a href="/docs/getting-started#installation" class="sidebar-link">Installation</a>
          <a href="/docs/getting-started#first-agent" class="sidebar-link">Your First Agent</a>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebar-group">
        <h3 class="sidebar-title">Guides</h3>
        <nav class="sidebar-nav">
          <a href="/docs/guides" class="sidebar-link">All Guides</a>
          <a href="/docs/guides#agents" class="sidebar-link">Creating Agents</a>
          <a href="/docs/guides#subagents" class="sidebar-link">Sub-Agents</a>
          <a href="/docs/guides#orchestration" class="sidebar-link">Mesh Orchestration</a>
        </nav>
      </div>

      <div class="sidebar-group">
        <h3 class="sidebar-title">Resources</h3>
        <nav class="sidebar-nav">
          <a href="/docs/api-reference" class="sidebar-link">API Reference</a>
          <a href="/docs/examples" class="sidebar-link">Examples</a>
          <a href="/blog" class="sidebar-link">Blog</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <article class="docs-content">
      <h1>Getting Started with CoderClaw</h1>
      
      <p class="lead">
        Welcome to CoderClaw! This guide will help you get up and running with the ultimate coding agent framework in just a few minutes.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>What is CoderClaw?</h2>
        <p>
          CoderClaw is an advanced framework for building autonomous coding agents that can manage complex development tasks independently. With CoderClaw, you transition from writing code to orchestrating intelligent agents that handle the work for you.
        </p>
        <p>
          At its core, CoderClaw enables you to:
        </p>
        <ul class="docs-list">
          <li>Create autonomous agents that code independently</li>
          <li>Manage multiple sub-agents working in parallel</li>
          <li>Orchestrate agent interactions via CoderClawLink mesh network</li>
          <li>Monitor and control agent behavior in real-time</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="installation">
        <h2>Installation</h2>
        <p>Get CoderClaw up and running on your system:</p>
        
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://coderclaw.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
        </div>

        <p>Or using the CLI directly:</p>
        
        <div class="code-block">
          <pre><code>npm install -g coderclaw</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="first-agent">
        <h2>Your First Agent</h2>
        <p>Let's create a simple agent that can perform basic code analysis:</p>

        <div class="code-block">
          <pre><code className="language-typescript">{`import { Agent, Task } from 'coderclaw';

const agent = new Agent({
  name: 'CodeAnalyzer',
  model: 'claude-opus',
  instructions: 'You are an expert code analyzer. Review code and provide detailed feedback.'
});

const result = await agent.run({
  task: 'Analyze this code and suggest improvements',
  input: 'const x = 1 + 2 + 3;'
});

console.log(result);`}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <p>That's it! Your first agent is running. Learn more about agent configuration in the <a href="/docs/guides#agents">Creating Agents</a> guide.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>
        <ul class="docs-list">
          <li><a href="/docs/guides">Read the comprehensive guides</a> to learn advanced features</li>
          <li><a href="/docs/api-reference">Check the API reference</a> for detailed documentation</li>
          <li><a href="/docs/examples">Explore example projects</a> to see CoderClaw in action</li>
          <li><a href="https://app.coderclaw.ai" target="_blank">Access the CoderClawLink dashboard</a> to manage your agents</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .docs-container {
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
  }

  .docs-sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 32px;
    position: sticky;
    top: 80px;
    height: fit-content;
  }

  .sidebar-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .sidebar-title {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .sidebar-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .sidebar-link {
    padding: 8px 12px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 14px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
  }

  .sidebar-link:hover {
    background: var(--surface-interactive);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .sidebar-link.active {
    background: var(--surface-interactive);
    border-left-color: var(--coral-bright);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .docs-content {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .docs-content h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .docs-content section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .docs-content section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .docs-content h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .docs-content p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .docs-content a {
    color: var(--coral-bright);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .docs-content a:hover {
    color: var(--coral-mid);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .docs-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 16px 0 24px 0;
  }

  .docs-list li {
    padding-left: 24px;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .docs-list li:before {
    content: 'â–¸';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--coral-bright);
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .code-block {
    background: var(--surface-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin: 16px 0 24px 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .code-block pre {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .code-block code {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .docs-container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 32px;
    }

    .docs-sidebar {
      position: static;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 24px;
      top: auto;
    }

    .docs-content h1 {
      font-size: 36px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .docs-container {
      padding: 24px 16px;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .docs-sidebar {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .docs-content h1 {
      font-size: 28px;
    }

    .docs-content h2 {
      font-size: 22px;
    }

    .lead {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
  }
</style>
